%h1 Pregnancy Support
%br
  .box
    %b MotherHeart Mentoring
    %p
      A faith-based mentorship in which a partner will be able to assist you
      through the pregnancy, birth, and parenting of your child. They can link you to many resources,
      including education, material needs, and adoption agency information if requested.
    %p
      = render 'phoneno'
      Contact Diane Bauman at 614-259-5318.
  %br
    .box
      %b Caring for 2
      %a{:href => "http://publichealth.columbus.gov/caring-for-2.aspx"}
        %span.btn.btn-lg.glyphicon.glyphicon-share-alt
      %p
        An in-home visitation program which helps you to access healthcare services, apply for
        WIC and Medicaid, and offer education on child development and parenting. Open to African-American
        women in zip codes 43201, 43203, 43205, 43206, 43207, 43209, 43211, 43215, and 43219.
      %p
        = render 'phoneno'
        614-645-7068.
    %br
      .box
        %b The Neighborhood House
        = render 'linkto', link: 'http://colsnhi.org/fhome/'
        %p
          Offers classes for expectant parents and parents of children up to age 24
          months. Topics cover community resources, alcohol  drugs, health, mental health, insurance, safety,
          fatherhood, goal setting, financial literacy, child development, and nutrition.
        %p
          = render 'phoneno'
          614-252-4941
        %p Location: 1000 Atcheson Street, 43203
